title: For Sale/Trade:  Mosin Nagant 91/59 Carbine
postcontent: For sale or trade I have a fairly uncommon Mosin Nagant 91/59 Carbine. This is probably cosmetically the nicest Soviet Mosin I have ever seen (and I own quite a few) but it doesn't fit in my current collecting focus and I want to free up some funds for other purchases. The 91/59 has a somewhat murky history, but what most people can agree on is that it they were shortened sometime after WW2 for use by police or internal security forces (the "we will make you talk comrade" variety) by Russia or one of the Soviet buffer states. What I can tell you for sure is that this rifle is SUPER nice. It has a nice deep rich blue and an incredible stock that is free of the usual Soviet flaky shellac. I'm not sure why the commies took such care on these carbines, but they actually did a heck of a good job. Only flaw in the wood are some compression dents on the left side below the reciever (it looks like from a rifle bolt being pressed against it while in a transport crate). While I personally prefer to keep it in original condition this would make a neat sporter rifle if you are so inclined due the reduced length.
